<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>URL Shortener — System Design</title>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com"/>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Syne:wght@400;600;700;800&family=DM+Mono:wght@400;500&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"/>
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #0a0a0f;
      --surface: #111118;
      --surface2: #1a1a24;
      --border: #2a2a38;
      --accent: #4f6ef7;
      --accent2: #a78bfa;
      --green: #34d399;
      --yellow: #fbbf24;
      --red: #f87171;
      --text: #e8e8f0;
      --muted: #6b6b8a;
      --heading-font: 'Syne', sans-serif;
      --body-font: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
      --mono-font: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    }

    * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

    body {
      background-color: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
      font-family: var(--body-font);
      font-size: 15px;
      line-height: 1.8;
    }

    /* Header */
    .hero {
      padding: 80px 40px 60px;
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    .hero-tag {
      display: inline-block;
      font-family: var(--mono-font);
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.15em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--accent);
      background: rgba(79,110,247,0.1);
      border: 1px solid rgba(79,110,247,0.25);
      padding: 4px 12px;
      border-radius: 99px;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }

    .hero h1 {
      font-family: var(--heading-font);
      font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 58px);
      font-weight: 800;
      line-height: 1.1;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #e8e8f0 0%, #a78bfa 100%);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
      background-clip: text;
    }

    .hero p {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 16px;
      max-width: 540px;
    }

    .hero-example {
      margin-top: 28px;
      padding: 16px 20px;
      background: var(--surface2);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      font-family: var(--mono-font);
      font-size: 13px;
    }

    .hero-example .label {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 11px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      margin-bottom: 4px;
    }

    .hero-example .url-long { color: var(--muted); }
    .hero-example .url-short { color: var(--green); margin-top: 8px; }
    .hero-example .arrow { color: var(--accent); margin: 4px 0; }

    /* Layout */
    .layout {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr;
      max-width: 1100px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      gap: 0;
    }

    /* TOC Sidebar */
    .toc {
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      height: 100vh;
      overflow-y: auto;
      padding: 40px 24px;
      border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    .toc-title {
      font-family: var(--mono-font);
      font-size: 10px;
      letter-spacing: 0.15em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    .toc a {
      display: block;
      font-size: 13px;
      color: var(--muted);
      text-decoration: none;
      padding: 5px 0;
      border-left: 2px solid transparent;
      padding-left: 10px;
      transition: all 0.2s;
    }

    .toc a:hover {
      color: var(--text);
      border-left-color: var(--accent);
    }

    /* Main content */
    .content {
      padding: 40px 60px 80px;
    }

    /* Sections */
    .section {
      margin-bottom: 60px;
      padding-bottom: 60px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    .section:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

    .section-tag {
      font-family: var(--mono-font);
      font-size: 10px;
      letter-spacing: 0.15em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--accent);
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    h2 {
      font-family: var(--heading-font);
      font-size: 26px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text);
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }

    h3 {
      font-family: var(--heading-font);
      font-size: 17px;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--text);
      margin: 24px 0 12px;
    }

    p { color: #b0b0cc; margin-bottom: 12px; }

    ul, ol {
      padding-left: 20px;
      color: #b0b0cc;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    li { margin-bottom: 4px; }

    /* Code blocks */
    pre {
      background: var(--surface2);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 20px 24px;
      overflow-x: auto;
      margin: 16px 0;
      position: relative;
    }

    pre code {
      font-family: var(--mono-font);
      font-size: 13px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: #c8c8e0;
    }

    .code-label {
      font-family: var(--mono-font);
      font-size: 10px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }

    code {
      font-family: var(--mono-font);
      font-size: 13px;
      background: var(--surface2);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding: 2px 6px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      color: var(--accent2);
    }

    pre code { background: none; border: none; padding: 0; color: #c8c8e0; }

    /* Cards grid */
    .card-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
      gap: 16px;
      margin: 20px 0;
    }

    .card {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 20px;
    }

    .card-icon {
      font-size: 22px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .card h4 {
      font-family: var(--heading-font);
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 6px;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .card p {
      font-size: 13px;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin: 0;
    }

    /* Tables */
    table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin: 16px 0;
      font-size: 14px;
    }

    th {
      font-family: var(--mono-font);
      font-size: 11px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      color: var(--muted);
      text-align: left;
      padding: 10px 16px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    td {
      padding: 12px 16px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      color: #b0b0cc;
    }

    tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
    tr:hover td { background: var(--surface2); }

    /* Badges */
    .badge {
      display: inline-block;
      font-family: var(--mono-font);
      font-size: 11px;
      padding: 3px 10px;
      border-radius: 99px;
      margin: 2px;
    }

    .badge-blue { background: rgba(79,110,247,0.15); color: #818cf8; border: 1px solid rgba(79,110,247,0.3); }
    .badge-green { background: rgba(52,211,153,0.12); color: #34d399; border: 1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.3); }
    .badge-yellow { background: rgba(251,191,36,0.12); color: #fbbf24; border: 1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.3); }
    .badge-red { background: rgba(248,113,113,0.12); color: #f87171; border: 1px solid rgba(248,113,113,0.3); }
    .badge-purple { background: rgba(167,139,250,0.12); color: #a78bfa; border: 1px solid rgba(167,139,250,0.3); }

    /* Two col */
    .two-col {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 16px;
      margin: 16px 0;
    }

    .info-box {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 16px 20px;
    }

    .info-box h4 {
      font-family: var(--heading-font);
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .info-box ul { margin: 0; }
    .info-box li { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); }

    /* Highlight box */
    .highlight {
      border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
      background: rgba(79,110,247,0.06);
      padding: 14px 18px;
      border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
      margin: 16px 0;
      font-size: 14px;
      color: #b0b0cc;
    }

    /* Flow diagram */
    .flow {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 0;
      margin: 16px 0;
    }

    .flow-step {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 12px;
    }

    .flow-box {
      background: var(--surface2);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 6px;
      padding: 8px 16px;
      font-family: var(--mono-font);
      font-size: 13px;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .flow-box.accent { border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--accent); }
    .flow-box.green { border-color: var(--green); color: var(--green); }

    .flow-arrow {
      width: 1px;
      height: 20px;
      background: var(--border);
      margin-left: 24px;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .toc { display: none; }
      .content { padding: 24px; }
      .two-col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .hero { padding: 40px 24px; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- Hero -->
<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-tag">System Design</div>
  <h1>URL Shortener</h1>
  <p>A scalable URL shortening service — from architecture to production trade-offs.</p>
  <div class="hero-example">
    <div class="label">Example</div>
    <div class="url-long">https://www.example.com/blog/system-design/url-shortener-guide</div>
    <div class="arrow">↓</div>
    <div class="url-short">https://short.ly/aZ91Kx</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="layout">

  <!-- TOC -->
  <nav class="toc">
    <div class="toc-title">Contents</div>
    <a href="#requirements">Requirements</a>
    <a href="#architecture">Architecture</a>
    <a href="#database">Database</a>
    <a href="#url-generation">URL Generation</a>
    <a href="#id-generation">ID Generation</a>
    <a href="#caching">Caching</a>
    <a href="#scaling">Scaling</a>
    <a href="#analytics">Analytics</a>
    <a href="#security">Security</a>
    <a href="#redirects">Redirect Types</a>
    <a href="#api">API Design</a>
    <a href="#tradeoffs">Trade-Offs</a>
    <a href="#techstack">Tech Stack</a>
    <a href="#conclusion">Conclusion</a>
  </nav>

  <!-- Content -->
  <main class="content">

    <!-- Requirements -->
    <div class="section" id="requirements">
      <div class="section-tag">01 — Requirements</div>
      <h2>Requirements</h2>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="info-box">
          <h4>Functional</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Create short URLs</li>
            <li>Redirect to original URLs</li>
            <li>Support custom aliases</li>
            <li>Optional expiration time</li>
            <li>Analytics tracking</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="info-box">
          <h4>Non-Functional</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>High availability</li>
            <li>Low latency</li>
            <li>Scalability</li>
            <li>Fault tolerance</li>
            <li>Durability &amp; Security</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Architecture -->
    <div class="section" id="architecture">
      <div class="section-tag">02 — Architecture</div>
      <h2>High Level Architecture</h2>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-icon">⚖️</div>
          <h4>Load Balancer</h4>
          <p>Distributes traffic across API and redirect servers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-icon">🔗</div>
          <h4>URL Shortener Service</h4>
          <p>Accepts long URLs, generates short codes, stores mappings.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-icon">↪️</div>
          <h4>Redirect Service</h4>
          <p>Fetches original URL and redirects the user instantly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-icon">🗄️</div>
          <h4>Database</h4>
          <p>Stores URL mappings, expiry, and click counts.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-icon">⚡</div>
          <h4>Redis Cache</h4>
          <p>Reduces DB load for frequently accessed URLs.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Database -->
    <div class="section" id="database">
      <div class="section-tag">03 — Database</div>
      <h2>Database Design</h2>
      <div class="code-label">Schema — url_mapping</div>
      <pre><code>CREATE TABLE url_mapping (
    id           BIGINT PRIMARY KEY,
    short_code   VARCHAR(10) UNIQUE,
    original_url TEXT,
    created_at   TIMESTAMP,
    expiry_at    TIMESTAMP,
    click_count  BIGINT
);</code></pre>
    </div>

    <!-- URL Generation -->
    <div class="section" id="url-generation">
      <div class="section-tag">04 — URL Generation</div>
      <h2>URL Generation Techniques</h2>

      <h3>1. Hashing</h3>
      <pre><code>MD5(long_url) -> xYz123</code></pre>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="info-box">
          <h4>✅ Advantages</h4>
          <ul><li>Simple</li><li>Deterministic</li></ul>
        </div>
        <div class="info-box">
          <h4>❌ Disadvantages</h4>
          <ul><li>Collision handling required</li><li>Predictable</li></ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>2. Base62 Encoding <span class="badge badge-green">Preferred</span></h3>
      <p>Character set: <code>[a-zA-Z0-9]</code></p>
      <pre><code>shortCode = encodeBase62(ID)
125 -> "cb"</code></pre>
      <div class="highlight">
        Base62 is URL-friendly, compact, and efficient. It avoids special characters that break URLs while keeping codes short enough to be shareable.
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ID Generation -->
    <div class="section" id="id-generation">
      <div class="section-tag">05 — ID Generation</div>
      <h2>ID Generation Strategies</h2>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="info-box">
          <h4>Auto Increment</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Simple to implement</li>
            <li>❌ Predictable &amp; insecure</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="info-box">
          <h4>Distributed IDs <span class="badge badge-blue">Recommended</span></h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Snowflake IDs</li>
            <li>UUIDs</li>
            <li>Randomized IDs + Base62</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Caching -->
    <div class="section" id="caching">
      <div class="section-tag">06 — Caching</div>
      <h2>Caching Strategy</h2>
      <p>Use Redis to reduce database load on frequently accessed short URLs.</p>
      <div class="flow">
        <div class="flow-step"><div class="flow-box accent">Request Short URL</div></div>
        <div class="flow-arrow"></div>
        <div class="flow-step"><div class="flow-box">Check Redis Cache</div></div>
        <div class="flow-arrow"></div>
        <div class="flow-step"><div class="flow-box green">Cache Hit → Return URL</div></div>
        <div class="flow-arrow"></div>
        <div class="flow-step"><div class="flow-box">Cache Miss → Query Database</div></div>
        <div class="flow-arrow"></div>
        <div class="flow-step"><div class="flow-box">Store in Cache → Return URL</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Scaling -->
    <div class="section" id="scaling">
      <div class="section-tag">07 — Scaling</div>
      <h2>Scaling the System</h2>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Horizontal Scaling</h4>
          <p>Add more API &amp; redirect servers behind a load balancer.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Read Replicas</h4>
          <p>Offload heavy reads and analytics queries to replicas.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Sharding</h4>
          <p>Shard by user ID or short code range to distribute data.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>CDN</h4>
          <p>Lower latency for popular URLs with global edge caching.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Analytics -->
    <div class="section" id="analytics">
      <div class="section-tag">08 — Analytics</div>
      <h2>Analytics Pipeline</h2>
      <p>Track clicks, browser, device, geolocation, and referrer asynchronously so it never blocks redirects.</p>
      <div class="flow">
        <div class="flow-step"><div class="flow-box accent">Redirect Service</div></div>
        <div class="flow-arrow"></div>
        <div class="flow-step"><div class="flow-box">Message Queue (Kafka)</div></div>
        <div class="flow-arrow"></div>
        <div class="flow-step"><div class="flow-box">Analytics Workers</div></div>
        <div class="flow-arrow"></div>
        <div class="flow-step"><div class="flow-box green">Analytics Database</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Security -->
    <div class="section" id="security">
      <div class="section-tag">09 — Security</div>
      <h2>Security Considerations</h2>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="info-box">
          <h4>Threats</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Spam &amp; abuse</li>
            <li>Malware links</li>
            <li>Phishing attacks</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="info-box">
          <h4>Solutions</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Rate limiting</li>
            <li>CAPTCHA</li>
            <li>URL validation &amp; blacklist scanning</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="highlight">
        Rate limiting uses Token Bucket or Leaky Bucket algorithms with counters stored in Redis. Example: 100 requests/minute/user.
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Redirect Types -->
    <div class="section" id="redirects">
      <div class="section-tag">10 — Redirects</div>
      <h2>Redirect Types</h2>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="info-box">
          <h4>301 — Permanent</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>✅ SEO friendly</li>
            <li>✅ Browser caching</li>
            <li>❌ Hard to modify later</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="info-box">
          <h4>302 — Temporary</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>✅ Flexible &amp; modifiable</li>
            <li>❌ Less caching efficiency</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- API -->
    <div class="section" id="api">
      <div class="section-tag">11 — API Design</div>
      <h2>API Design</h2>

      <h3>Create Short URL</h3>
      <div class="code-label">POST /shorten</div>
      <pre><code>// Request
{ "url": "https://example.com/very-long-url" }

// Response
{ "shortUrl": "https://short.ly/abc123" }</code></pre>

      <h3>Redirect</h3>
      <div class="code-label">GET /{shortCode}</div>
      <pre><code>301 Redirect → Original URL</code></pre>

      <h3>Analytics</h3>
      <div class="code-label">GET /analytics/{shortCode}</div>
      <pre><code>{ "clicks": 4821, "topCountry": "IN", "device": "mobile" }</code></pre>
    </div>

    <!-- Trade-offs -->
    <div class="section" id="tradeoffs">
      <div class="section-tag">12 — Trade-Offs</div>
      <h2>Trade-Offs</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Choice</th>
            <th>Advantage</th>
            <th>Drawback</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="badge badge-blue">SQL Database</span></td>
            <td>Strong consistency</td>
            <td>Harder to scale</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="badge badge-purple">NoSQL Database</span></td>
            <td>High scalability</td>
            <td>Eventual consistency</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="badge badge-yellow">Sequential IDs</span></td>
            <td>Simple implementation</td>
            <td>Predictable &amp; insecure</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="badge badge-green">Random IDs</span></td>
            <td>Secure</td>
            <td>Collision handling needed</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- Tech Stack -->
    <div class="section" id="techstack">
      <div class="section-tag">13 — Tech Stack</div>
      <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Layer</th><th>Technology</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Backend</td><td><span class="badge badge-green">Node.js</span> <span class="badge badge-blue">Go</span> <span class="badge badge-purple">Java</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Database</td><td><span class="badge badge-blue">PostgreSQL</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Cache</td><td><span class="badge badge-red">Redis</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Queue</td><td><span class="badge badge-yellow">Kafka</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Load Balancer</td><td><span class="badge badge-green">NGINX</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Monitoring</td><td><span class="badge badge-purple">Prometheus + Grafana</span></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- Conclusion -->
    <div class="section" id="conclusion">
      <div class="section-tag">14 — Conclusion</div>
      <h2>Conclusion</h2>
      <p>A URL shortener is a classic distributed systems problem. The key pillars are:</p>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <div class="card"><h4>Base62 Encoding</h4><p>Compact, URL-safe short codes.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h4>Distributed IDs</h4><p>Secure, non-predictable generation.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h4>Redis Caching</h4><p>Low-latency redirects at scale.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h4>Async Analytics</h4><p>Never block the redirect path.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h4>Horizontal Scaling</h4><p>Handle billions of URLs reliably.</p></div>
